Karamat Ali ( born 18 March 1996 ) is a Pakistani first - class cricketer .
Jeremy Coller ( born 17 May 1958 ) is a British financial executive and philanthropist .
Emperor Huan of Han ( Chinese : 漢桓帝 ; pinyin : Hàn Húan Dì ; Wade -- Giles : Han Huan - ti ; 132 - -168 ) was the 27th emperor of the Han Dynasty after he was enthroned by the Empress Dowager and her brother Liang Ji on 1 August 146 .
Sadichha Shrestha ( Nepali : सदिच्छा श्रेष्ठ ) ( born 23 November 1991 , in Kathmandu ) is Miss Nepal 2010 .
Gareth John ( born 17 January 1972 ) is a former Australian rules footballer who played with the Sydney Swans and North Melbourne in the Australian Football League ( AFL ) .
Smail Tulja ( born Smajo Džurlić in Plav , Montenegro , Yugoslavia , in 1940 or 1941 ) is a Montenegrin who was convicted in a Montenegro court , in July 2010 , for the 1990 murder of Mary Beal in New York City .
Željko Reiner ( born 28 May 1953 ) is a Croatian physician , politician and university professor , member of The Croatian Academy of Sciences and Arts , former Minister of Health and Social Welfare who serves as the 10th Speaker of the Croatian Parliament since December 28 , 2015 .
Frank Condon , MA , MFA , ( b. Derbyshire , England , 1943 ) is a playwright and theatrical production director , the founding Artistic Director of River Stage , in Sacramento , California , and a professor of theatre at Cosumnes River College .
Atso Almila ( born 13 June 1953 , in Helsinki1 ) is a Finnish orchestral conductor , musical director , composer , trombonist and teacher .

Otto Göbl ( born 16 September 1936 ) was a West German bobsledder who competed from the late 1950s to the early 1960s .

Jonathan Littell ( born 10 October 1967 ) is a writer living in Barcelona .

Sabri Raheel ( Arabic : صبري رحيل‎ ) ( born on 2 October 1987 ) is an Egyptian footballer who plays as a Left - back for Egyptian Premier League side Al Ahly .
Richard Neile ( 1562 - -1640 ) was an English churchman , bishop successively of six English dioceses , more than any other man , including the Archdiocese of York from 1631 until his death .
Jim Main ( born 1943 ) is a sports journalist and writer from Australia .
Bruce Jensen ( born 1962 in Indianapolis , Indiana ) is a US illustrator who has created book covers for science fiction authors such as Kim Stanley Robinson , Neal Stephenson , Charles Sheffield , Joe Haldeman , Linda Nagata , and Philip K. Dick .
Phil Callaway , who has achieved notoriety for his humorous writing and speaking , was born July 26 , 1961 in Three Hills , Alberta , Canada .

Muhammad Izzdin Shafiq bin Yacob ( born 14 December 1990 ) known as Izzdin Shafiq is a Singaporean footballer who plays for Tampines Rovers .

Father Willie Doyle , S.J. , MC or William Joseph Gabriel Doyle ( 3 March 1873 -- 16 August 1917 ) , was an Irish Jesuit priest who was killed in action during the First World War .
Stefano Tilli ( born 22 August 1962 ) is a retired Italian sprinter trained by Fabrizio Lepore , who specialized in the 100 and 200 m. He is a two - time European indoor champion , three - time semi - finalist at the Olympic Games , and was the world record holder in the 200 m indoor .
John C. McCullough ( 1858 -- February 28 , 1920 ) was the Attorney General of California from 1863 to 1867 .
Ibrahim Lamorde ( born 20 December 1962 ) is a Nigerian police officer who was appointed Acting Chairman of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission ( EFCC ) on 23 November 2011 after chairman Farida Waziri had been dismissed by President Goodluck Jonathan .
Anders Annerfalk ( born 1959 in Sweden ) is an aviation author , historian and PR Director .

Vernon Carkeek ( 13 February 1893 -- 28 December 1968 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Vitaly Bugrov ( Russian Виталий Иванович Бугров , 14 May 1938 -- 23 June 1994 ) was a notable Russian science fiction editor , critic , and bibliographer , one of the founders of the Soviet science - fiction fandom .
Gilles Roux ( born January 20 , 1971 ) is a French speedcuber primarily known for inventing a 3x3 method , the Roux Method , and achieving fast solves with it .
Angela Platt ( born 29 May 1979 , Coleraine , County Londonderry ) is a field hockey goalkeeper from Northern Ireland , who made her international debut for the Women 's National Team in 2000 against the United States .
Pierre Jean Louis Ovide Doublet ( 25 August 1749 - 4 February 1824 ) was a French politician and writer who spent much of his life serving in the Knights of Malta .

Wyatt Rainey Blassingame ( 6 February 1909 -- 1985 ) , a.k.a . W.B. Rainey , was the author of more than 600 short stories and articles for national magazines , four adult novels and dozens of juvenile nonfiction books .
Lars Spuybroek ( born September 16 , 1959 , Rotterdam ) is a Dutch architect , artist and author .

Walter Parfrey ( 1882 - 1918 ) was an Irish hurler who played as a goalkeeper for the Cork senior team .
J. Heinrich Matthaei ( born 4 May 1929 ) is a German biochemist .

Sara Ahmed ( 30 August 1969 ) , is a British - Australian academic working at the intersection of feminist theory , queer theory , critical race theory and postcolonialism .

Joseph Hueber , ( 1715 or 1717 -- 1787 ) , was a significant Austrian baroque master builder who studied under Johann Lukas von Hildebrandt .
Marco Coledan ( born 22 August 1988 ) is an Italian road and track racing cyclist riding for Trek Factory Racing .
Jack Savoretti ( born 10 October 1983 ) is an Italian - English solo acoustic singer .
Fabrizio Faglioli ( born c. 1925 ( age 89 - -90 ) ) is an Italian professional rugby league footballer of the 1950s playing at representative level for Italy , and at club level for Torino XIII , as a Loose forward / Lock , i.e. number 13 , during the era of contested scrums .
Jenny Sages is an Archibald Prize peoples choice award winning Australian artist born 1933 in Shanghai , China .
Angel Otero ( born 1981 in San Juan , Puerto Rico ) is a contemporary visual artist specializing in painting .
Giovanni Luca Conforti ( 1560 -- May 11 , 1608 ) was an Italian composer and prominent falsetto singer who wrote an exercise book about Baroque embellishments , Breve et facile maniera d'essercitarsi ad ogni scolaro or Brief and easy manner of exercising for every student , still in use today .
Eros Bagnara ( born 27 April 1985 ) is a former Italian professional footballer who plays for Italian Prima Categoria club Edo Mestre RSM .
Hun Manith ( Khmer : ហ៊ុន ម៉ាណិត ; born 17 October 1981 ) is a brigadier general in the Royal Cambodian Armed Forces ( RCAF ) and the fourth child of Prime Minister Hun Sen. His older brother , Hun Manet , is a lieutenant general in the RCAF .
James Doolin ( 1932 - -2002 ) was an American painter and muralist best known for his saturated natural and urban southern California landscapes .
Eva von Trott ( 1505 - 1567 ) , was the royal mistress of Henry V , Duke of Brunswick - Lüneburg , from 1522 until 1567 .

In computer programming , a Visual Basic Extension ( commonly abbreviated VBX ) or custom control , was the component model used in Microsoft Visual Basic versions 1.0 to 3.0 .
Grabbed by the Ghoulies is an action - adventure video game developed by Rare and published by Microsoft Studios for the Xbox .
OpenRefine , formerly called Google Refine , is a standalone open source desktop application for data cleanup and transformation to other formats , the activity known as data wrangling .
Valtric is a vertically scrolling shoot 'em up arcade game , released in 1986 by Jaleco .

Grand Theft Auto Online is a persistent , open world online multiplayer video game developed by Rockstar North and published by Rockstar Games .
The Alchemy ( microarchitecture ) is a low power microprocessor design developed by Alchemy Semiconductor implementing the MIPS32 instruction set by MIPS Technologies .
Sandvox is a WYSIWYG template - based website creation tool by Karelia Software , based on WebKit .
The Pentium III ( marketed as Intel Pentium III Processor , informally PIII , also stylized as Pentium ! ! ! ) brand refers to Intel 's 32-bit x86 desktop and mobile microprocessors based on the sixth - generation P6 microarchitecture introduced on February 26 , 1999 .

The Taifa of Valencia was a medieval taifa kingdom which existed , in and around Valencia , Spain during four distinct periods : from 1010 to 1065 , from 1075 to 1099 , from 1145 to 1147 and last from 1229 to 1238 when it was finally conquered by the Aragon .
James Shears and Sons was a firm of London coppersmiths and braziers who were active from c1785 to 1891 .

The Fifth Republic of South Korea was the government of South Korea from 1979 to 1987 , replacing the Fourth Republic of South Korea .
Aster Società Italiana Motori was an Italian manufacturer of automobiles from 1906 - 1908 .
The Union of Populars ( Greek : Ένωσις Λαϊκών ) was a coalition of Greek right - wing political parties for the elections of 1958 .

The Bornu Empire ( 1380 - -1893 ) was a state of what is now northeastern Nigeria from 1380 to 1893 .
Moscow Governorate ( Russian : Московская губерния ; pre - reform Russian : Московская губернiя ) , or the Government of Moscow , was an administrative division ( a guberniya ) of the Tsardom of Russia , the Russian Empire , and the Russian SFSR , which existed in 1708 - -1929 .
Hafslund Nycomed is a defunct company that existed between 1986 and 1996 after the power and industry company Hafslund had bought the pharmaceutical company Nycomed .
Since discontinuing all scheduled service in May 2008 , North American Airlines continued to operate until 2014 as solely a charter airline .
The State of the Presidi ( Italian Stato dei Presidi , meaning `` state of the garrisons '' ) was a small state ( 300 km2 ) in Italy between 1557 and 1801 .
The Königsberg Public Library was destroyed in August 1944 during the Bombing of Königsberg in World War II .
Southern Han ( simplified Chinese : 南汉 ; traditional Chinese : 南漢 ; pinyin : Nán Hàn ) was a kingdom that existed during the Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms period ( 907 - 960 ) along China 's southern coast from 917 to 971 .
From 1 July 2015 , the Department of Immigration and Border Protection and the Australian Customs and Border Protection Service were consolidated into a single Department of Immigration and Border Protection .
The Prince - Bishopric of Hildesheim ( German : Hochstift Hildesheim ) was a state of the Holy Roman Empire from the Middle Ages until 1803 .
The Pahlavi dynasty ( Persian : دودمان پهلوی‎‎ ) was the ruling house of Iran from 1925 until 1979 , when the monarchy was overthrown and abolished as a result of the Iranian Revolution .
PC Bruno was a Polish - French signals intelligence station near Paris during World War II , from October 1939 until June 1940 .

The Janoir was a French automobile manufactured from 1921 until 1922 by a motorcycle and sidecar company in Saint - Ouen .
The Polish Academy of Literature ( Polish : Polska Akademia Literatury , PAL ) was one of the most important state institutions of literary life in the Second Polish Republic , operating between 1933 - -1939 with the headquarters in Warsaw .
Vesy ( Russian : Весы́ ; English : The Balance or The Scales ) was a Russian symbolist magazine published in Moscow from 1904 to 1909 , with the financial backing of philanthropist S. A. Polyakov .
The International Marxist Group ( IMG ) was a Trotskyist group in Britain between 1968 and 1982 .
The Michel Irat was a French automobile manufactured from 1929 until 1930 in Paris .
Confederate Arizona was a territory claimed by the Confederate States of America during the American Civil War , between 1861 and 1865 .
The Woermann - Linie was a German shipping company that operated from 1885 to 1941 .
Chimor ( also Kingdom of Chimor ) was the political grouping of the Chimú culture that ruled the northern coast of Peru , beginning around 850 and ending around 1470 .
Lechmere ( /ˈliːtʃmɪər/ ; sometimes described as Lechmere 's ) was a New England retail store that closed in 1997 .
Infinity Broadcasting Corporation was a radio company that existed from 1972 until 2005 .
Weingarten Abbey or St. Martin 's Abbey ( German : Reichsabtei Weingarten until 1803 , then merely Abtei Weingarten ) is a Benedictine monastery on the Martinsberg ( St. Martin 's Mount ) in Weingarten near Ravensburg in Baden - Württemberg ( Germany ) .
On 31 March 1924 the assets and operations of Handley Page Transport were merged with three other British airlines to found Imperial Airways .

Erica Yuen graduated from St. Stephen 's College , Hong Kong in 1997 , and she continued her education at Tufts University in Massachusetts , and graduated summa cum laude .

Bill Nichols is Professor Emeritus in the Cinema Department at San Francisco State University and Chair of the Documentary Film Institute advisory board .
Sarah Cullen ( 6 October 1949 -- 22 January 2012 ) was a British radio and television journalist who worked for ITN , as well as BBC Radio 4 's Today programme .
Rim Turkmani is a Syrian - born astrophysicist at Imperial College London and Dorothy Hodgkin Research Fellow of the Royal Society .
Anne Fausto - Sterling ( born July 30 , 1944 ) is the Nancy Duke Lewis Professor of Biology and Gender Studies at Brown University .

Hatshepsut was the daughter of Thutmose I and his primary wife Ahmes .
Przemysł II was the fifth child and only son of Duke Przemysł I of Greater Poland and his wife Elisabeth , daughter of Duke Henry II the Pious of Silesia .
Lady Agnes Campbell ( 1526 - -1601 ) was the daughter of Colin Campbell , 3rd Earl of Argyll and his wife Lady Jean Gordon .
John Sherman was born in Lancaster , Ohio , May 10 , 1823 , to Charles Robert Sherman and his wife , Mary Hoyt Sherman , the eighth of their eleven children .
Æthelswith ( c. 838 - 888 ) was the only known daughter of King Æthelwulf of Wessex .
David Wallechinsky was born David Wallace in Los Angeles to a Jewish family , the son of writer Sylvia Kahn and the author and screenwriter Irving Wallace .
Mithridates I Callinicus ( Greek : Μιθριδάτης ὀ Кαλλίνικος ) was a king of Orontid Armenian descent who lived between 2nd century BC and 1st century BC . Mithridates was a prince , the son and successor of King of Commagene , Sames II Theosebes Dikaios .

It is located on the border between the municipalities of Vang and Vågå , ( in Oppland ) , but the northwestern corner of the municipality of Øystre Slidre reaches the summit of Øystre Rasletind .
CJNE - FM is a privately owned Canadian radio station that broadcasts an incredibly diverse oldies / adult hits / classic rock format , branded as The Storm , at 94.7 FM in Nipawin , Saskatchewan .
Gręzówka ( ɡrɛ̃ˈzufka ) is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Łuków , within Łuków County , Lublin Voivodeship , in eastern Poland .
The Sonnenberg Tunnel is a 1,550 m long motorway tunnel , constructed between 1971 and 1976 and located in Lucerne , Switzerland .
Morayfield State High School is a public , coeducational high school in Morayfield , Queensland , Australia .
Phillips - Sprague Mine , also known as the Beckley Exhibition Coal Mine , is a historic coal mine located at New River Park in Beckley , Raleigh County , West Virginia .
Taos Regional Airport ( IATA : TSM , ICAO : KSKX , FAA LID : SKX ) is a public - use airport located eight nautical miles ( 15 km ) northwest of the central business district of Taos , in Taos County , New Mexico , United States .
The Amway Center is a sports and entertainment venue in Orlando , Florida , located in the Downtown area .
Aasa Buttar is a small village located in the Giddarbaha Tehsil of Sri Muktsar Sahib district of Eastern Punjab .
Harmony Union School District is a public school district based in Occidental , California which feeds into the West Sonoma County Union High School District .
The Larkin Building was a 110-floor , 368.2 meters ( 1,208 ft ) tall skyscraper that was proposed in 1926 and canceled in 1930 at 330 West 42nd Street in New York City , New York , United States .
WGDQ ( 93.1 FM , `` WGDQ '' ) is a radio station licensed to serve the community of Sumrall , Mississippi , USA , and serving the Laurel - Hattiesburg area .
WIVR 101.7 FM is a radio station licensed to Kentland , Indiana , and serving Newton County , Benton County , and Jasper County in Indiana , and Iroquois County , and Kankakee County in Illinois .
The Winchester Model 54 is a bolt - action rifle manufactured by the Winchester Repeating Arms Company .
The Vympel NPO R-77 missile ( NATO reporting name : AA-12 Adder ) is a Russian medium range , active radar homing air - to - air missile system .
ADC Cirrus engines were originally built by ADC Aircraft until Cirrus Aero Engines Limited was formed in 1927 .
The VAZ-2106 is an automobile which was produced by the Russian manufacturer AvtoVAZ , later by Russian IZh and Ukrainian Anto - Rus .
The Type 072-class landing ship ( NATO designation Yukan class ) are large landing ships built by Shanghai - based Zhonghua Shipyard ( now Hudong - Zhonghua Shipbuilding ) in the 1980s to replace the aging World War II - era ex - US Navy L-1511 tank landing ships in service with the PLA Navy .
The Breguet Type IV was an aircraft built by Breguet Aviation .
With over 3,000 manufactured by Loewe and Deutsche Waffen und Munitionsfabriken , Borchardt C-93 was the first mass - produced semi - automatic pistol .
The Lake - class patrol vessel was a class of patrol vessels built in 1974 for the Royal New Zealand Navy by the British boat builders Brooke Marine .
The TGV 001 was an experimental gas turbine - electric locomotive - powered trainset built by Alstom to break speed records between 250 - -300 kilometres per hour ( 160 - -190 mph ) .
The Ascari Ecosse is a mid - engine sports car produced by Ascari Cars from 1998 to 1999 .
The Enstrom 480 is a small , light helicopter produced by the Enstrom Helicopter Corporation .
The Yamaha SR250 is a single cylinder motorcycle made by Yamaha Motor Company from 1980 to 1982 for the first generation , and since 2001 for the second generation .
The SM U-118 was commissioned on 8 May 1918 , following her construction at the AG Vulcan Stettin shipyard in Hamburg .
The Hyundai BlueOn is a subcompact 5-door hatchback electric car produced by Hyundai Motor Company .
The P-800 Oniks ( Russian : П-800 Оникс ; English : Onyx ) , also known in export markets as Yakhont ( Russian : Яхонт ; English : ruby ) , is a Soviet / Russian supersonic anti - ship cruise missile developed by NPO Mashinostroyeniya as a ramjet version of P-80 Zubr .
The Le Rhône 9J is a nine - cylinder rotary aircraft engine produced in France by Gnome et Rhône .
The Colt Machine Gun-1 or CMG-1 was an open bolt belt - fed machine gun that fired 5.56×45 mm cartridges designed by Colt Manufacturing Company in 1965 .
Great Western 60 is a 2 - 8 - 0 consolidation built in August 1937 by the American Locomotive Company in Schenectady , New York , and is currently operated on the Black River & Western Railroad ( BR&W ) in Ringoes , New Jersey .
Hydra - Shok is a type of cartridge with expanding bullets made by Federal Cartridge .
The Mitsubishi Colt 600 is a five - seat , two - door passenger sedan produced by Shin Mitsubishi Heavy - Industries , Ltd - one of the companies which would become Mitsubishi Motors .
The GM PD-4501 Scenicruiser , manufactured exclusively by General Motors for The Greyhound Corporation , was a three - axle monocoque two - level coach used by Greyhound from July 1954 into the mid-70 's .
USS America ( ID-3006 ) was a troop transport for the United States Navy during World War I. She was launched in 1905 as SS Amerika by Harland and Wolff in Belfast for the Hamburg America Line of Germany .
The Pilatus PC-7 Turbo Trainer is a low - wing tandem - seat training aircraft , manufactured by Pilatus Aircraft of Switzerland .
HMQS Midge was specifically built in England by J. Samuel White , Cowes , for this purpose and shipped out to Australia in 1887 .
The Hyundai Universe ( hangul:현대 유니버스 ) is a heavy - duty luxury coach built by Hyundai Motor Company .
The Israeli Ordnance Corps are responsible for final Merkava assembly .
Histria Prince was built by the Constanța Shipyard in 2008 as a 40,416 DWT ship used for the transportation of oil and oil products and chemical products .
The Caparo T1 is a British mid - engine , rear - wheel drive , two - seat automobile built by Caparo Vehicle Technologies , founded by design director Ben Scott - Geddes and engineering director Graham Halstead , engineers formerly involved in the development of the McLaren F1 .
The Marlin Model 336 is a lever - action sporting rifle and carbine made by Marlin Firearms .
BrahMos - II or BrahMos-2 or BrahMos Mark II ( note : not to be confused with BrahMos block-2 ) is a hypersonic cruise missile currently under joint development by Russia 's NPO Mashinostroeyenia and India 's Defence Research and Development Organisation , which have together formed BrahMos Aerospace Private Limited .
The HP Prime is a graphing calculator manufactured by Hewlett - Packard ( HP ) .
The SPAD S.XIII was a French biplane fighter aircraft of World War I , developed by Société Pour L'Aviation et ses Dérivés ( SPAD ) from the earlier highly successful SPAD S.VII .
The DB Class 101 is a class of three - phase electric locomotives built by Adtranz and operated by DB Fernverkehr in Germany .
MV Derbyshire was an ore - bulk - oil combination carrier built in 1976 by Swan Hunter , as the last in the series of the Bridge - class sextet .
When Commodore International was liquidated in 1994 , a number of prototypes were sold on the open market , and thus a few people actually own a Commodore 65 .
MS Mediterranean Sky was an ocean liner built in 1953 by Vickers Shipbuilding and Engineering , Barrow - in - Furness , United Kingdom as City of York .
The SS Athenic was a British passenger liner built by Harland & Wolff shipyards for the White Star Line in 1901 .

Conotton Creek ( pronounced kah - NOT - en ) is a tributary of the Tuscarawas River , 38.7 miles ( 62.3 km ) long , in eastern Ohio in the United States .
Accokeek Creek is a tidal tributary of Potomac Creek , itself a tributary of the Potomac River , in Stafford County , Virginia , United States .
The Yalgar River is a 185-kilometre - long tributary of the Murchison River , located in the Shire of Meekatharra in central Western Australia .

The Wölpe is a left tributary of the river Aller in the German state of Lower Saxony and is about 22 km long .
Cabriel ( Spanish : ( kaˈβɾjel ) ) or Cabriol ( Valencian : ( kaβɾiˈɔɫ ) ) is a tributary of Júcar River .
The river Brend is a right - bank tributary of the Fränkische Saale ( Franconian Saale ) , in Lower Franconia , Bavaria , Germany .
The Cenepa River currently rises in the Cordillera del Cóndor mountain range in Peru , South America and has a length of 185 km . The Cenepa flows into the Marañón River at Orellana .
Salzersgraben is a tributary of the Erlenbach river in Bavaria , Germany .
The Dease River flows through northwestern British Columbia , Canada and is a tributary of the Liard River .
Fojnička rijeka is a left tributary of the Bosna in Bosnia and Herzegovina .
The Boyer River is a tributary of the Missouri River , 118 miles ( 190 km ) long , in western Iowa in the United States .
The Kuolajoki River originates in the Lake Kuolajarvi in Russia and flows into the Tenniöjoki River in Finland .
Then the Dischmabach flows in a northwesterly direction through the elongated and gently sloping Dischma valley and flows into the Landwasser between Davos Dorf and Davos Platz .
The Firehole River is located in northwestern Wyoming , and is one of the two major tributaries of the Madison River .
The Hoback River , also called the Fall River , is an approximately 55-mile ( 89 km)-long tributary of the Snake River in the U.S. state of Wyoming .
The Purnach River is a tributary to the Ponoy River on the Kola Peninsula , Russia .
Oslava is a river in the Czech Republic , the left tributary of the Jihlava River .
The McArthur River is a river in the Northern Territory of Australia which flows into the Gulf of Carpentaria at Port McArthur , opposite the Sir Edward Pellew Group of Islands .
Weeks Creek is a small creek tributary to La Honda Creek , which in turn is tributary to San Gregorio Creek in western San Mateo County , California .
Aubette de Meulan is a French river that begins at Avernes in Val - d'Oise , flows through Vigny , and empties into the Seine in Meulan - en - Yvelines .
The Dysna ( Belarusian : Дзісна Dzisna ; Russian : Дисна Disna ) is a river that flows through Lithuania and Belarus into the Daugava River near the town of Dzisna .
The Genil River is the main ( left ) tributary of the river Guadalquivir in Andalusia , Spain .
The Moruya River flows generally east , joined by two minor tributaries , past the town of Moruya , before reaching its mouth of the Tasman Sea at Moruya Heads .
After 62 km , the Pascua River ends in a wide delta that empties into the Baker Channel , previously having rushed in a last area of rapids .
The Boone River is a tributary of the Des Moines River in north - central Iowa in the United States .
Formed from the confluence of the Horse Creek and Teatree Creek , the Wang Wauk River rises on the slopes of the Meyers Range within Wang Wauk State Forest , and flows generally north and then east , joined by one minor tributary before reaching its confluence with the Coolongolook River , southwest of Nabiac .
Moody Brook is a small watercourse that flows into Stanley Harbour on East Falkland , Falkland Islands .
The Mushawe River ( alternative spelling Mushawi River ) is a right - bank tributary of the Mwenezi River in Zimbabwe .
The Black Kei River , ( Afrikaans : Swart - Keirivier ) , originates southwest of Queenstown , and eventually joins the White Kei River , to become the Great Kei River .
The Tuscarawas River is a principal tributary of the Muskingum River , 129.9 miles ( 209 km ) long , in northeastern Ohio in the United States .
The Sierra Leone River is a river estuary on the Atlantic Ocean in Western Sierra Leone .
The Bouès , is a right tributary of the Arros , at the eastern end of the basin of the Adour , in the Southwest of France .
The Ounasjoki River ( Northern Sami : Ovnnesjohka ) is the Kemijoki River 's largest tributary and is Finland 's longest single river tributary .
Pyakupur River ( Russian : Пякупур ) is a river in Yamalo - Nenets Autonomous Okrug , Russia , the left tributary of the Pur River .
In mathematical analysis , Lipschitz continuity , named after Rudolf Lipschitz , is a strong form of uniform continuity for functions .
The Turing test is a test , developed by Alan Turing in 1950 , of a machine 's ability to exhibit intelligent behavior equivalent to , or indistinguishable from , that of a human .
A Riemann problem , named after Bernhard Riemann , consists of an initial value problem composed of a conservation equation together with piecewise constant data having a single discontinuity .
Sequent calculus is , in essence , a style of formal logical argumentation where every line of a proof is a conditional tautology ( called a sequent by Gerhard Gentzen ) instead of an unconditional tautology .
The Lincoln Highway was America 's first national memorial to President Abraham Lincoln , predating the 1922 dedication of the Lincoln Memorial in Washington , D.C. , by nine years .

In mathematics , Marden 's theorem , named after Morris Marden but proven much earlier by Jörg Siebeck , gives a geometric relationship between the zeroes of a third - degree polynomial with complex coefficients and the zeroes of its derivative .

The Romance of Maoriland was a 1930 New Zealand film , intended to be New Zealand 's first `` talkie '' film with Ted Coubrays Coubraytone sound system , though also having intertitles .
The Flying Scissors is a 2009 mockumentary that follows eight entrants in the a fictional National Rock Paper Scissors League ( NRPSL ) Championship .

The Tree 's Knees is a 1931 one - reel short subject featuring Bosko , part of the Looney Tunes series .
The Journal of Religious & Theological Information is a peer - reviewed academic journal published by Routledge that covers research in the field of library and information studies as relating to religious studies and related fields , including philosophy , ethnic studies , anthropology , sociology , and history .
The Journal of NeuroInterventional Surgery is a peer - reviewed medical journal published by the BMJ Group covering the field of neurointerventional surgery .
Neuroscience & Biobehavioral Reviews is a peer - reviewed scientific journal covering behavioral neuroscience published by Elsevier .
The Harvard Asia Pacific Review is a biannual academic journal covering the Asia - Pacific Region and edited by students at Harvard University .

Aurora Reyes Flores ( born in Hidalgo del Parral , September 9 , 1908 -- Mexico City , April 26 , 1985 ) was a Mexican painter , as well as the first female exponent of Mexican muralism .
Duygu Ulusoy ( aka : Duygu Gül Ulusoy ; born April 24 , 1987 in Garmisch - Partenkirchen , West Germany ) , is a female Turkish skier competing in the alpine discipline .

Badureliya Sports Club is a first - class cricket team in Sri Lanka .
Mara Fullin ( born in Venice , 13 January 1965 ) is a former Italian basketball player .
Shi Tingmao ( Chinese : 施廷懋 ; pinyin : Shī Tíngmào ; born 31 August 1991 ) is a Chinese diver representing Chongqing diving team .
Kjøbenhavns Skøjteløberforening ( English : Copenhagen Ice Skating Club ) , commonly known as KSF , are a Danish ice hockey team in Copenhagen currently playing in the third tier Danish ice hockey league , the second division .
The 2007 Belgian Figure Skating Championships ( Dutch : Belgisch Kampioenschap 2007 ; French : Championnat de Belgique 2007 ) were the Belgian Figure Skating Championships of the 2006 - 2007 figure skating season .

Lillian Hoban ( May 18 , 1925 -- July 17 , 1998 ) was an American illustrator and children 's writer best known for picture books created with other writers including her husband Russell Hoban .

Empress Xiaomucheng ( died 17 February 1808 ) was the first consort of the Daoguang Emperor of the Qing Dynasty .

Jane Howard , Duchess of Norfolk ( née Bickerton ; 1643/4 - 28 August 1693 ) , was the wife of Henry Howard , 6th Duke of Norfolk .

Margaret Fownes - Luttrell ( 7 February 1726 -- 13 August 1766 ) was an English artist and wife of Henry Fownes Luttrell .
Anna van Egmont ( March 1533 -- 24 March 1558 ) was a wealthy Dutch heiress who became the first wife of William the Silent , Prince of Orange .
Ebbe Rode was married to actress Helle Virkner .
Margaret of Prades ( 1388/95 -- 23 July 1429 ) was the queen consort of Aragon as a wife of the King Martin of Aragon .
Maud de Ufford , Countess of Oxford ( 1345/1346 -- 25 January 1413 ) was a wealthy English noblewoman and the wife of Thomas de Vere , 8th Earl of Oxford .

Mabel FitzRobert , Countess of Gloucester ( 1090 -- 29 September 1157 ) was an Anglo - Norman noblewoman , and a wealthy heiress who brought the lordship of Gloucester , among other prestigious honours to her husband , Robert , 1st Earl of Gloucester upon their marriage .
Saira Elizabeth Luiza Shah died on 15th Aug 1960 , according to her tombstone in the Muslim section of the cemetery at Brookwood , Woking , Surrey , England where she , Ikbal Ali - Shah and other members of the Shah family are buried .

Princess Ingeborg Magnusdotter of Sweden , ( b. 1277 , Sweden -- d. 5 April or 15 August 1319 ) , was a Danish queen consort , daughter of king Magnus III of Sweden and wife of king Eric VI of Denmark .
Adelaide Gail Zappa ( née Sloatman ; January 1 , 1945 -- October 7 , 2015 ) was the wife of musician and composer Frank Zappa and the trustee of the Zappa Family Trust .
Olivia Langdon Clemens ( November 27 , 1845 -- June 5 , 1904 ) was the wife of the famous American author Samuel Langhorne Clemens , better known as Mark Twain .
Alice Dudley , Duchess of Dudley ( née Leigh ; 1579 -- 22 January 1669 ) , also known as Duchess Dudley , was the second wife of the explorer Sir Robert Dudley .
Kamptobaatar is a Mongolian mammal genus from the Upper Cretaceous .
Acanthogonatus confusus is a mygalomorph spider of Argentina and Chile , its name referring to the confusion between this species and A. subcalpeianus .
Lactarius vinaceorufescens , commonly known as the yellow - staining milkcap or the yellow - latex milky , is a poisonous species of fungus in the family Russulaceae .
Micranthes ferruginea is a species of saxifrage known by the common names russethair saxifrage and rusty saxifrage .
Notocrater craticulatus is a southern , cold - water , deepwater species of limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Pseudococculinidae , one of the families of false limpets .
Geraldine Farrar ( February 28 , 1882 -- March 11 , 1967 ) was an American soprano opera singer and film actress , noted for her beauty , acting ability , and `` the intimate timbre of her voice . ''
Emma Nevada ( née Wixom ) ( 7 February 1859 -- 20 June 1940 ) was an American operatic soprano particularly known for her performances in operas by Bellini and Donizetti and the French composers Ambroise Thomas , Charles Gounod , and Léo Delibes .
David Banderali ( Palazzolo sull'Oglio , January 12 , 1789 - Paris , 13 June 1849 ) was an Italian tenor , popular in France in the nineteenth century .
Aida Navarro ( born October 17 , 1937 ) , is a Venezuelan mezzo soprano , born in Caracas .
Emil Scaria ( September 18 , 1838 -- July 23 , 1886 ) was an Austrian bass - baritone .
